  "prompt": "Indian Air Force: Can I stay with my family during the service after long hours of duty (daily) if not on leave?",
  "response": "In the Indian Air Force (IAF), the policies regarding staying with family during service hours can vary based on several factors, including your posting, the specific duties of your role, and the regulations of the unit you are serving in. Generally, personnel are required to adhere to their duty hours and may not be able to stay with family during long working hours unless they are on leave or if they have specific permissions that allow for family accommodation.\n\nIn many cases, if you are stationed at a base where family accommodation is available, you may be able to stay with your family provided you are not on duty. However, during certain operational or training periods, staying with family may be restricted to ensure operational readiness and safety.\n\nIf you have specific concerns, it's best to consult your commanding officer or the administrative section at your base for detailed information related to your situation and the applicable policies.",
